alerts.description:
THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN FRANCISCO BAY AREA HAS ISSUED AN
* URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY FOR...
SANTA CLARA COUNTY IN NORTHERN CALIFORNIA...
ALAMEDA COUNTY IN NORTHERN CALIFORNIA...
CONTRA COSTA COUNTY IN NORTHERN CALIFORNIA...
SANTA CRUZ COUNTY IN NORTHERN CALIFORNIA...
SAN MATEO COUNTY IN NORTHERN CALIFORNIA...
SAN FRANCISCO COUNTY IN NORTHERN CALIFORNIA...
* UNTIL 830 PM PST.
* AT 534 PM PST AUTOMATED RAINGAGE AND DOPPLER RADAR DATA INDICATED
HEAVY RAINFALL MOVING OVER THE ADVISORY AREA. NUMEROUS TRAFFIC
HAZARDS AND ROADWAY FLOODING CONDITIONS ARE PRESENT ACROSS THE URBAN
CORRIDOR OF THE GREATER SF BAY AREA.
EXCESS RUNOFF FROM HEAVY RAINFALL IS EXPECTED TO CAUSE PONDING OF
WATER IN URBAN AREAS...HIGHWAYS...STREETS AND UNDERPASSES AS WELL AS
OTHER POOR DRAINAGE AREAS AND LOW LYING SPOTS. ALSO...SMALL CREEKS
AND STREAMS COULD FLOOD QUICKLY...POSSIBLY COVERING ROADS AND NEARBY
LOW AREAS.
ALLOW EXTRA TIME TO GET TO YOUR DESTINATION. IF WATER COVERS THE
ROADWAY DO NOT CROSS IT. FLOOD WATERS ARE USUALLY DEEPER THAN THEY
APPEAR AND THE WATER MAY BE TOO DEEP TO ALLOW YOUR VEHICLE TO CROSS
SAFELY.
TO REPORT FLOODING...HAVE THE NEAREST LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY RELAY
YOUR REPORT TO THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE FORECAST OFFICE.
alerts.title: Flood Advisory for San Francisco, CA

alerts.description:

IS LIKELY TO ENSUE AS RAINFALL INCREASES.
